pokemons.description: It attacks with rapid beats of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more pumped.
pokemons.name: Grookey

pokemons.description: When it’s drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won’t even notice that it’s already knocked out its opponent.
pokemons.name: Thwackey

pokemons.description: The one with the best drumming techniques becomes the boss of the troop. It has a gentle disposition and values harmony among its group.
pokemons.name: Rillaboom

pokemons.description: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it’s raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.
pokemons.name: Scorbunny

pokemons.description: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.
pokemons.name: Raboot

pokemons.description: It’s skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.
pokemons.name: Cinderace

pokemons.description: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokémon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.
pokemons.name: Sobble

pokemons.description: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.
pokemons.name: Drizzile

pokemons.description: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes’ weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.
pokemons.name: Inteleon

pokemons.description: It eats berries nonstop—a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It’ll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.
pokemons.name: Skwovet

pokemons.description: Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.
pokemons.name: Greedent

pokemons.description: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.
pokemons.name: Rookidee

pokemons.description: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent’s strength.
pokemons.name: Corvisquire

pokemons.description: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region’s airborne taxi service.
pokemons.name: Corviknight

pokemons.description: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.
pokemons.name: Blipbug

pokemons.description: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.
pokemons.name: Dottler

pokemons.description: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what’s around it—and what’s around it can include things over six miles away.
pokemons.name: Orbeetle

pokemons.description: Cunning and cautious, this Pokémon survives by stealing food from others. It erases its tracks with swipes of its tail as it makes off with its plunder.
pokemons.name: Nickit

pokemons.description: With a lithe body and sharp claws, it goes around stealing food and eggs. Boltund is its natural enemy.
pokemons.name: Thievul

pokemons.description: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.
pokemons.name: Gossifleur

pokemons.description: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn—a Galar regional specialty.
pokemons.name: Eldegoss

pokemons.description: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won’t be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.
pokemons.name: Wooloo

pokemons.description: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
pokemons.name: Dubwool

pokemons.description: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.
pokemons.name: Chewtle

pokemons.description: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.
pokemons.name: Drednaw

pokemons.description: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.
pokemons.name: Yamper

pokemons.description: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.
pokemons.name: Boltund

pokemons.description: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.
pokemons.name: Rolycoly

pokemons.description: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.
pokemons.name: Carkol

pokemons.description: While it’s engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.
pokemons.name: Coalossal

pokemons.description: As soon as it’s born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.
pokemons.name: Applin

pokemons.description: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.
pokemons.name: Flapple

pokemons.description: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.
pokemons.name: Appletun

pokemons.description: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.
pokemons.name: Silicobra

pokemons.description: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.
pokemons.name: Sandaconda

pokemons.description: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.
pokemons.name: Cramorant

pokemons.description: After it’s eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That’s when Cramorant swallows it up.
pokemons.name: Arrokuda

pokemons.description: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.
pokemons.name: Barraskewda

pokemons.description: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.
pokemons.name: Toxel

pokemons.description: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.
pokemons.name: Toxtricity

pokemons.description: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they’re well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.
pokemons.name: Sizzlipede

pokemons.description: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.
pokemons.name: Centiskorch

pokemons.description: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn’t alarmed when that happens—it knows they’ll grow back. It’s about as smart as a three-year-old.
pokemons.name: Clobbopus

pokemons.description: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.
pokemons.name: Grapploct

pokemons.description: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.
pokemons.name: Sinistea

pokemons.description: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist.
pokemons.name: Polteageist

pokemons.description: If this Pokémon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.
pokemons.name: Hatenna

pokemons.description: Using the braids on its head, it pummels foes to get them to quiet down. One blow from those braids would knock out a professional boxer.
pokemons.name: Hattrem

pokemons.description: If you’re too loud around it, you risk being torn apart by the claws on its tentacle. This Pokémon is also known as the Forest Witch.
pokemons.name: Hatterene

pokemons.description: It sneaks into people’s homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.
pokemons.name: Impidimp

pokemons.description: With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.
pokemons.name: Morgrem

pokemons.description: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.
pokemons.name: Grimmsnarl

pokemons.description: It evolved after experiencing numerous fights. While crossing its arms, it lets out a shout that would make any opponent flinch.
pokemons.name: Obstagoon

pokemons.description: After many battles, it evolved dangerous claws that come together to form daggers when extended.
pokemons.name: Perrserker

pokemons.description: Be cautious of the ectoplasmic body surrounding its soul. You’ll become stiff as stone if you touch it.
pokemons.name: Cursola

pokemons.description: After deflecting attacks with its hard leaf shield, it strikes back with its sharp leek stalk. The leek stalk is both weapon and food.
pokemons.name: Sirfetch’d

pokemons.description: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.
pokemons.name: Mr. Rime

pokemons.description: Never touch its shadowlike body, or you’ll be shown the horrific memories behind the picture carved into it.
pokemons.name: Runerigus

pokemons.description: They say that any patisserie visited by Milcery is guaranteed success and good fortune.
pokemons.name: Milcery

pokemons.description: When Alcremie is content, the cream it secretes from its hands becomes sweeter and richer.
pokemons.name: Alcremie

pokemons.description: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.
pokemons.name: Falinks

pokemons.description: It stores electricity in each spine. Even if one gets broken off, it still continues to emit electricity for at least three hours.
pokemons.name: Pincurchin

pokemons.description: It eats snow that piles up on the ground. The more snow it eats, the bigger and more impressive the spikes on its back grow.
pokemons.name: Snom

pokemons.description: It shows no mercy to any who desecrate fields and mountains. It will fly around on its icy wings, causing a blizzard to chase offenders away.
pokemons.name: Frosmoth

pokemons.description: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.
pokemons.name: Stonjourner

pokemons.description: This Pokémon keeps its heat-sensitive head cool with ice. It fishes for its food, dangling its single hair into the sea to lure in prey.
pokemons.name: Eiscue

pokemons.description: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.
pokemons.name: Indeedee

pokemons.description: It carries electrically roasted seeds with it as if they’re precious treasures. No matter how much it eats, it always gets hungry again in short order.
pokemons.name: Morpeko

pokemons.description: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokémon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.
pokemons.name: Cufant

pokemons.description: These Pokémon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.
pokemons.name: Copperajah

pokemons.description: The powerful muscles in its tail generate its electricity. Compared to its lower body, its upper half is entirely too small.
pokemons.name: Dracozolt

pokemons.description: This Pokémon lived on prehistoric seashores and was able to preserve food with the ice on its body. It went extinct because it moved so slowly.
pokemons.name: Arctozolt

pokemons.description: Its mighty legs are capable of running at speeds exceeding 40 mph, but this Pokémon can’t breathe unless it’s underwater.
pokemons.name: Dracovish

pokemons.description: The skin on its face is impervious to attack, but breathing difficulties made this Pokémon go extinct anyway.
pokemons.name: Arctovish

pokemons.description: The special metal that composes its body is very light, so this Pokémon has considerable agility. It lives in caves because it dislikes the rain.
pokemons.name: Duraludon

pokemons.description: If this weak Pokémon is by itself, a mere child could defeat it. But if Dreepy has friends to help it train, it can evolve and become much stronger.
pokemons.name: Dreepy

pokemons.description: Without a Dreepy to place on its head and care for, it gets so uneasy it’ll try to substitute any Pokémon it finds for the missing Dreepy.
pokemons.name: Drakloak

pokemons.description: Apparently the Dreepy inside Dragapult’s horns eagerly look forward to being launched out at Mach speeds.
pokemons.name: Dragapult

pokemons.description: This Pokémon has slumbered for many years. Some say it’s Zamazenta’s elder sister—others say the two Pokémon are rivals.
pokemons.name: Zacian

pokemons.description: This Pokémon slept for aeons while in the form of a statue. It was asleep for so long, people forgot that it ever existed.
pokemons.name: Zamazenta

pokemons.description: It was inside a meteorite that fell 20,000 years ago. There seems to be a connection between this Pokémon and the Dynamax phenomenon.
pokemons.name: Eternatus
